[Student "S"]
{You dealt this hand.  

You are not strong enough to open 1NT, but too strong to pass. You bid 1\D. Partner responds 1NT. What do you say next? 

You are not strong enough to open 1NT, but too strong to pass. You bid 1\D. Partner responds 1NT. What do you say next?

With that small doubleton in \Cs it is very tempting to rescue partner from 1NT by bidding 2\S. There are three good reasons why you don't. First, bidding 1\D followed by 2\S is a <b>REVERSE</b>, which shows a strong hand, perhaps 16-17 points or more. Second, and even more important, partner's 1NT bid <b>DENIES</b> a 4-card Major suit. And third, partner probably has something in \Cs since he has no 4-card Major and also didn't feel like supporting your \Ds.

So you pass and hope for the best.}

